I did this with gperf, and it's not a huge win (20% startup speed
improvement, or so) but it is faster.  See my patch (including the
*very* very nice (IMHO) menu rewrite and animation enhancements) from my
web site.  I believe I posted the patch (to 2.0.45) here, as well, a
couple months ago.  Its available at:

http://www.cs.washington.edu/homes/gjb/patches/fvwm-2.0.45-menus-animation-gjb.patch

The most important thing I wrote is complete fixing of the menu code to
allow greater and more orthogonal flexibility and *much* MUCH cleaner
keyboard navigation of the menus.  Automatic assignments of shortcuts
still needs to be added, but long menus are split into cascaded shorter
menus as they are created (e.g., the xlock menu from TheNextLevel is too
long to fit on my 1024x768 screen).

I'd really love to see my patches in a new version before 2.1.0.

